      <t>&lt;p&gt;This memo describes a backward-compatible technique that may be used by OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) implementations to advertise unavailability to forward transit traffic or to lower the preference level for the paths through such a router.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
